<?xml version = "1.0"?>
<content>
   <intro>
      <page>
         <left>
            <line>Arcane Refraction allows creation</line>
            <line>of mulitblock structures called</line>
            <line>lenses. Active lens creates </line>
            <line>powerful AOE effects below it.</line>
            <line>Thier purpose is to help with</line>
            <line>farming and boost resource</line>
            <line>generation.</line>
         </left>
      </page>
   </intro>

   <basics>
      <page>
         <left>
            <line>A lens is a flat, circular multi-</line>
            <line>block. Center of the structure</line>
            <line>always must be a Focus block.</line>
            <line>Rest of the lens is made of</line>
            <line>Dispersive blocks of the</line>
            <line>same type as Focus. Any</line>
            <line>Dispersive block can be replaced</line>
            <line>with a Filter block if an effect</line>
            <line>requires it.</line>
            <line></line>
            <line>Amethyst Focus can be crafted with</line>
            <line>an Amethyst Block, Spyglass, </line>
            <line>2 blocks of Blue Ice, 3 glowing</line>
            <line>ink sacs and 2 nautilus shells.</line>
            <line>#-85#150#minecraft:blue_ice#minecraft:spyglass#minecraft:blue_ice#minecraft:glow_ink_sac#minecraft:amethyst_block#minecraft:glow_ink_sac#minecraft:nautilus_shell#minecraft:glow_ink_sac#minecraft:nautilus_shell</line>
         </left>
         <right>
            <line>Dispersive Amethyst can be</line>
            <line>crafted with 4 amethyst blocks,</line>
            <line>2 soul soil blocks, 2 dripstone</line>
            <line>blocks, and a fire charge.</line>
            <line>#38#90#minecraft:soul_soil#minecraft:amethyst_block#minecraft:soul_soil#minecraft:amethyst_block#minecraft:fire_charge#minecraft:amethyst_block#minecraft:dripstone_block#minecraft:amethyst_block#minecraft:dripstone_block</line>
            <line></line>
            <line></line>
            <line></line>
            <line></line>
            <line></line>
            <line></line>
            <line></line>
            <line>Amethyst Filter can be crafted</line>
            <line>from Dispersive Amethyst with</line>
            <line>use of stonecutter.</line>
            <line></line>
            <line>A lens can be one of 5 sizes.</line>
            <line>Check 'Lens Sizes' chapter for</line>
            <line>diagrams.</line>
         </right>
      </page>
      <page>
         <left>
            <line>Before a constructed lens can</line>
            <line>be activated, Focus must be</line>
            <line>filled with one type of coating,</line>
            <line>which decides what effect lens</line>
            <line>will be spreading. To coat a</line>
            <line>lens of size n, the n-th row</line>
            <line>from top as well as all previous</line>
            <line>rows inside Focus GUI must be</line>
            <line>completely filled with single</line>
            <line>type of coating. When the lens</line>
            <line>is ready right-click the Focus</line>
            <line>while holding a Brush to </line>
            <line>activate it.</line>
            <line></line>
            <line>Entire surface of a lens requires</line>
            <line>sky access in order to work.</line>
            <line>Lenses do not block sky access</line>
            <line>therefore can be stacked on top</line>
            <line>of eachother.</line>
         </left>
         <right>
            <line>A lens affects all blocks</line>
            <line>underneath unless blocked</line>
            <line>by a block that can not be</line>
            <line>affected, up to vertical</line>
            <line>range of 15 blocks. Range can</line>
            <line>be changed in mods configuration.</line>
            <line></line>
            <line>Amethyst lenses have diffrent</line>
            <line>effects during day than night.</line>
            <line>Any lens can be turned off</line>
            <line>with redstone signal.</line>
            <line>Therefore daylight sensor can</line>
            <line>be used to control effects of</line>
            <line>amethyst lenses.</line>
            <line></line>
            <line>Amethyst lens parts can be</line>
            <line>transformed into Regolith or</line>
            <line>Tephra parts.</line>
            <line>Check 'Transformations' chapter</line>
            <line>for more infromation.</line>
         </right>
      </page>
   </basics>
   
